<P>
MORNING REPORT: WEDDING BELLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Actor Griffin O'Neal and Rima Belinda Uranga became husband and wife in a Las 
Vegas wedding chapel ceremony before about 60 guests over the weekend. The 
bridegroom's father, Ryan O'Neal, was among those attending the Sunday night 
ceremony at the Candelight Wedding Chapel and later threw the newlywed couple a 
reception at the Dunes Hotel. O'Neal, 24, served a 15-day prison sentence 
earlier this year for violating terms of probation for his involvement in the 
1986 boating death of the son of director Francis Coppola.ALEENE MacMINN 
