<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: WHITTIER; 
</P>
<P>
2 RESTAURANTS PRAISED FOR HIRING DISABLED WORKERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Whittier Union High School District has recognized two local fast-food 
restaurants for hiring and training disabled students and adults, school 
officials announced. 
</P>
<P>
At a luncheon and awards ceremony recently, officials of the district's Career 
Assessment and Placement Center cited Carl's Jr., on East Rosecrans Avenue in 
La Mirada, and Wienerschnitzel, on Leffingwell Road in Whittier, for teaching 
work skills to local disabled people, district spokeswoman Ann M. Garten said. 
</P>
<P>
Workers at the Career Assessment and Placement Center, a model program in the 
district, counsel disabled people, show them how to adjust to a work 
environment, guide them into careers and place them in jobs, Garten said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
