<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: FREEWAY LANE TO BE CLOSED FOR BRIDGE WORK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At least one northbound lane of the Antelope Valley Freeway in Lancaster will 
be closed for the next month while state Department of Transportation workers 
repair a bridge hit by a truck that was too tall to pass under it. 
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, crews planned to close the northbound side of the freeway 
overnight between the Avenue F on-ramp and a point half a mile south of Avenue 
H to begin the project and put in new striping and traffic markers. 
</P>
<P>
Resident engineer Andrew Ponzi said Caltrans would try to keep at least one 
lane open at all times during work on the Avenue G overcrossing, which has been 
shut down since it was hit last year by a truck. 
</P>
<P>
But the repairs may require complete shutdowns of the northbound lanes and 
detours of traffic to Sierra Highway before the project is completed in early 
August, Ponzi said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
