<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: SHERIFF'S TEAMS CALL OFF SEARCH FOR FISHERMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles County Sheriff's rescue teams have abandoned their search for a 
fisherman presumed drowned when he reportedly fell into the California Aqueduct 
near Gorman early Tuesday, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
California State Police who regularly patrol the aqueduct will continue to look 
for the man, described as being in his 60s, Sheriff's Sgt. Ron Boudreaux said. 
</P>
<P>
A fishing companion told deputies he heard a splash and saw the man floating 
downstream in the swift water, Boudreaux said. Sheriff's divers were unable to 
find the victim, and deputies called off their search at 4:30 p.m. Tuesday. 
Authorities are withholding the man's identify. 
</P>
</TEXT>
