<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hauke Fuhlbruegge of East Germany upset Olympic champion Peter Rono of Kenya in 
the 1,500 meters at the Olympic Day Mobil Grand Prix track and field meet in 
East Berlin. 
</P>
<P>
Fuhlbruegge won with a strong kick in 3 minutes 36.87 seconds. Rono was second 
in 3:37.15, and another Kenyan, Kip Cheruyiot, was third in 3:37.72. 
</P>
<P>
American winners included Henry Thomas of UCLA in the 200 meters with a time of 
20.61 seconds, Tom Simon in the 400 with a time of 45.04, and Tonie Campbell in 
the 110-meter hurdles with a time of 13.48. Jan Wohlschlag was the only 
American woman to win an event, clearing 6 feet 4 1/4 inches in the high jump. 
</P>
