BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Elders IXL Managers Say Buyout Near: Elders IXL Ltd. Chairman John Elliott and 
other executives said they were close to completing a buyout bid for the 
Australian brewing company through their privately held firm, Harlin Holdings. 
Elliott said Harlin, which currently owns a 34% fully diluted stake in Elders, 
is arranging financing for a stock swap that values the company at $4.08 
billion. He added that Harlin is expected to make an announcement before an 
Elders shareholders meeting on July 27. Elders is part of a group helping Los 
Angeles investor Alfred Checchi finance his $4.05-billion bid for NWA, the 
parent of Northwest Airlines. 
</P>
