WESTSIDE DIGEST: SANTA MONICA; 
</P>
<P>
OUTSTANDING EDUCATORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Seven Santa Monica College instructors have been named Outstanding Educators by 
the Academic Senate's professional committee. 
</P>
<P>
The honored instructors for the 1988-89 academic year are Joan Barker, 
anthropology; Anna Biller, physical education; Dick Dodge, English; Alan Jon, 
cosmetology; Don Murray, mathematics; LeDonna Shouse, interior design, and Mary 
Jane Weil, disabled students counseling. 
</P>
<P>
Nominations for the awards were made by students and faculty members, and 
selections were made by a committee of students and instructors in each 
academic division. 
</P>
<P>
Winners of the awards receive $250 from the Academic Senate and a $250 voucher 
from the college to be used toward purchase of educational materials or 
conference attendance. 
</P>
