<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE STATE; 
</P>
<P>
HOLIDAY TRAFFIC TAKES 78 LIVES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The California Highway Patrol reported 78 traffic deaths over the long Fourth 
of July weekend. Officers also made 2,857 arrests for driving while 
intoxicated. Of the traffic deaths reported in CHP jurisdictions, 49 victims 
were not wearing seat belts. The holiday period for this year's Independence 
Day weekend lasted 4 1/2 days, and is not comparable to the 3 1/2 days for 
1988, the CHP noted. The last comparable period was in 1985, when 71 motorists 
were killed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
