<HEADLINE>
<P>
CINCINNATI BELL BUYS TELEMARKETING FIRM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CINCINNATI 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cincinnati Bell Inc. said Wednesday that it has acquired the telemarketing 
company Automated Phone Exchange Inc. of Salt Lake City. 
</P>
<P>
Apex, founded in 1979, is a privately held company offering inbound 
telemarketing services using toll-free 800 lines, as well as outbound services. 
</P>
<P>
The Apex operation will be merged with the NICE Corp. of Ogden, Utah, to form a 
new entity, NICE-Apex. 
</P>
<P>
The new company will be headed by the president of NICE, Seldon O. Young, and 
will continue to operate as a division of Matrixx Marketing Inc., a Cincinnati 
Bell subsidiary. Apex management will join NICE management to lead the new 
company. 
</P>
</TEXT>
