<P>
SANTA ANA ROBBERY SUSPECT SHOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Santa Ana police officer shot a robbery suspect in the leg at about 2:30 a.m. 
today, hours after three men held up the Bobkin Bar at 2521 S. Main St. and 
fled with $150. 
</P>
<P>
The wounded man was identified as Ramon Soto, 20, of Santa Ana, said Santa Ana 
police spokeswoman Maureen Thomas. He was treated at Western Medical Center and 
transferred to the Orange County Jail, she said. 
</P>
<P>
Police did not release the name of the officer. 
</P>
<P>
The incident began when three men walked into the bar at 11:15 p.m. Wednesday 
and stole $150, Thomas said. Police investigators who had been called to the 
scene found an AK-47 that was apparently used during the robbery and obtained 
the address of one of the suspects from a customer, Thomas said. 
</P>
<P>
They went to the address in Santa Ana, and Soto confronted them at the 
driveway, Thomas said. 
</P>
<P>
"Officers told him to stop, but he fled on foot, and they continued asking him 
to stop," Thomas said. "One of our officers fired one shot from his shotgun. It 
struck the suspect in the leg." 
</P>
<P>
Two other suspects were arrested at the address. Thomas declined to immediately 
release their names, saying that "it would hamper an ongoing investigation." 
</P>
</TEXT>
